13: Why am I always... the odd one out?
16:
I knew, then and there, that I still
hadn't found a single scrap of
courage within me.
22: By the will of the Stars, I order you...
33:
That gate's probably not big enough
for everyone to get through, so we'll
look for another way.
35:
I'm not sure if we'll make it... But in
the meantime, can I count on you to
handle things?
39:
...All right. You have to promise
though—
43:
I'll make it back safe and sound.
Promise.
52:
Worried about everyone inside,
yeah? Let's split up and gather 'em
all!
71:
I wished to be more like you children
and do my own part... Although I'm
running out of fuel now.
75:
...We should head to the roof. There's
an escape route—
85:
Not that it matters... Wherever we
go, it's all over already—
91:
No, it's not! We're still alive and
kicking, aren't we?
94: I'll get us out of this!
115:
...I talked a big game, but in the end,
I didn't actually do much.
117:
Mr. Takamori was the one who
handled gathering the Shibuya
residents and meeting the
representatives from Palpebra.
125:
Surprising, right? Without him, I don't
think everything would've gone so
smoothly.
130:
Hey, you shouldn't underestimate
our old Teach! He knows how to get
a job done!
135:
Aren't you the one who laughed and
said, "RIP," when I told you he was
gonna be my homeroom teacher?
139:
I dunno, my memory's a little fuzzy
on that one.
143:
I'm pretty sure you said something
like, "I want to snap his glasses in
half," before.
148:
Okay, that was definitely not me!
Talk about violent, sheesh!
157:
Well, hold on. I get it. He could use a
pair with a better design.
167:
So then... The reason why you
wanna join the Guild Knights...
172: I'm tired of standing on the sidelines.
174:
The next time something threatens
my home and the people I care
about, I want to do something about
it.
177:
I've got to take my own step forward,
just like you have, Ayumu.
185:
Aaaand there it is! Ayumu's
trademark humbleness!
191:
At least let me finish my sentence!
And what do you mean by
trademark?!
203:
It's part of why I look up to him as
my hero.
208:
...I get why you'd say that, but listen...
Back in middle school, I was only—
215:
A lot has happened since then. I'm
probably just projecting a lot of my
own feelings...
218:
But heroes don't usually call
themselves heroes, right? It's up to
other people to decide.
233:
Even heroes can make mistakes
and disappoint people, right?
238:
I dunno what you're talking about,
but now I'm getting pissed! The heck
is that supposed to mean?!
248:
That's the second time you've said
that today!
252:
Most of all, I think I can believe in
myself now.
256:
The courage I've been searching
for... was inside me all along.
